                            <comment id="14142709" author="adityakishore" created="Sun, 21 Sep 2014 21:08:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This seems to be partially incorrect&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Adding the following configuration to &lt;tt&gt;hbase-site.xml&lt;/tt&gt; has no effect&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&amp;lt;property&amp;gt;
  &amp;lt;name&amp;gt;hadoop.proxyuser.$USER.groups&amp;lt;/name&amp;gt;
  &amp;lt;value&amp;gt;$GROUPS&amp;lt;/value&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/property&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;property&amp;gt;
  &amp;lt;name&amp;gt;hadoop.proxyuser.$USER.hosts&amp;lt;/name&amp;gt;
  &amp;lt;value&amp;gt;$GROUPS&amp;lt;/value&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/property&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;as &lt;tt&gt;ProxyUsers.authorize()&lt;/tt&gt; internally calls &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/hadoop-common/blob/branch-2.4/hadoop-common-project/hadoop-common/src/main/java/org/apache/hadoop/security/authorize/ProxyUsers.java#L52&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;refreshSuperUserGroupsConfiguration()&lt;/a&gt; which initializes proxy configuration from the default HBase configuration files (and HBase configuration files are never added to the static default configuration source list).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To workaround this, user must add these to one of the hadoop default properties (core-site.xml).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can fix this by calling &lt;tt&gt;ProxyUsers.refreshSuperUserGroupsConfiguration(conf);&lt;/tt&gt; in the REST server initialization code, where &lt;tt&gt;conf&lt;/tt&gt; is created as &lt;tt&gt;Configuration conf = HBaseConfiguration.create();&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Does it make sense? If yes, will create a JIRA and attach the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14142831" author="adityakishore" created="Mon, 22 Sep 2014 01:44:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-12045&quot; title=&quot;REST proxy users configuration in hbase-site.xml is ignored&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-12045&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-12045&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14143414" author="jxiang" created="Mon, 22 Sep 2014 16:57:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You also need to add the following &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;  &amp;lt;property&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;name&amp;gt;hadoop.security.authorization&amp;lt;/name&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;value&amp;gt;true&amp;lt;/value&amp;gt;
  &amp;lt;/property&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Adding the following configuration to hbase-site.xml has no effect&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It works for me. I didn&apos;t touch core-site.xml.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14143433" author="adityakishore" created="Mon, 22 Sep 2014 17:08:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I did add the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;hadoop.security.authorization&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; property. That&apos;s how everything else worked except where &lt;tt&gt;ProxyUsers&lt;/tt&gt; class failed to load the group and host configuration from hbase-site.xml.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As you can see, if &lt;tt&gt;ProxyUsers.refreshSuperUserGroupsConfiguration(conf);&lt;/tt&gt; is not invoked with a specific configuration, ProxyUsers.authorize(), internally calls &lt;tt&gt;ProxyUsers.refreshSuperUserGroupsConfiguration()&lt;/tt&gt; which instantiate a &lt;tt&gt;new Configuration();&lt;/tt&gt; which would not load HBase configuration resources.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14143448" author="jxiang" created="Mon, 22 Sep 2014 17:17:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I see. Do you mean the doAs option in the REST server side?  The documentation didn&apos;t mention this feature at all.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14143498" author="adityakishore" created="Mon, 22 Sep 2014 17:39:36 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Do you mean the doAs option in the REST server side?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yes. Isn&apos;t this the feature these two settings mean to control? I do not see any other purpose.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;The documentation didn&apos;t mention this feature at all.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But it does mention the settings which control this &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14143513" author="jxiang" created="Mon, 22 Sep 2014 17:46:25 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Isn&apos;t this the feature these two settings mean to control? I do not see any other purpose.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s meant to be used in HBase server side (such as RS), so that when the REST server accesses HBase on behalf of a client, these configurations provide some control.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14143522" author="adityakishore" created="Mon, 22 Sep 2014 17:51:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You are right! Somehow I lost the sight of the fact that this single setting can control both, especially if both daemons are running as the same user.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In my case, I was running RS/Master as &apos;hbase&apos; and the REST server as &apos;rest&apos; user.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14330575" author="enis" created="Sat, 21 Feb 2015 23:29:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing this issue after 0.99.0 release. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
